TOGGLE
  Set or report your nation's behavior flags.

SYNTAX
  toggle
  toggle <flag>
  toggle <flag> on|off
  togg   <flag> [on|off]

DESCRIPTION
  With no argument, reports the on/off status of every flag.
  With just a flag name, flips it (on->off, off->on).
  With a flag name and on/off, forces it to that state.

  <flag> matches on the first letter too, same as 4.4.1 (e.g. "c" for
  coastwatch).

  FLAGS
    inform      i   notify inline when a telegram arrives
    flash       f   client-side hint: flash on incoming message
    beep        b   client-side hint: beep on incoming message
    coastwatch  c   sectors passively watch for foreign ships (below)
    sonar       s   client-side hint: enable sonar-related alerts
    techlists   t   client-side hint: show tech-transfer lists

  Of these, only coastwatch currently changes server behavior. The
  others are stored and reported for client use, matching their
  mostly client-hint role in 4.4.1 -- toggling them costs nothing and
  is safe to leave on.

  COASTWATCH
  When on, every owned sector passively reports sighting a foreign
  ship within its vision range (baseline 4 hexes, or 14 for a radar
  installation, tech/efficiency-scaled) -- as long as your relation
  to that ship's owner is Neutral or worse. You get a telegram
  ("<Nation> <ship type> sighted at X,Y") once per sighting nation
  per step; it never reveals the ship's uid, only its owner and
  type. This is purely informational and separate from whether a
  fortress will actually fire on that ship (see 'info navigate' for
  the fort auto-fire gauntlet, which is gated on Hostile relations,
  not on coastwatch or any sighting at all).

EXAMPLE
  toggle                  show status of all six flags
  toggle coastwatch       flip coastwatch
  toggle c on             force coastwatch on
  toggle coastwatch off   force coastwatch off

SEE ALSO
  navigate  relations  declare  fire  telegram
